<section id="step1" class="doc-section">
  <div class="doc-section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="step-label">Step 1</p>
      <p>Search for MiKTeX and open the official homepage.</p>
      <p>If MiKTeX is already installed, skip to Step 4. If TeX Live is installed, remove it first.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="https://miktex.org/">MiKTeX homepage</a>
    </div>
    <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-1.png" alt="MiKTeX homepage"></figure>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="step2" class="doc-section">
  <div class="doc-section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="step-label">Step 2</p>
      <p>Download the installer for your operating system.</p>
    </div>
    <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-2.png" alt="MiKTeX download page"></figure>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="step3" class="doc-section">
  <div class="doc-section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="step-label">Step 3</p>
      <p>Run the Basic MiKTeX Installer. Proceed with the default options.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="figure-stack">
      <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-3.png" alt="MiKTeX installer"></figure>
      <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-4.png" alt="MiKTeX installation steps"></figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="step4" class="doc-section">
  <div class="doc-section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="step-label">Step 4</p>
      <p>Open MiKTeX Console, go to the Packages tab, search for <code>latexmk</code>, and install it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="figure-stack">
      <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-5.png" alt="MiKTeX console"></figure>
      <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-6.png" alt="Installing latexmk"></figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="step5" class="doc-section">
  <div class="doc-section-grid">
    <div>
      <p class="step-label">Step 5</p>
      <p>Windows users should also install Strawberry Perl. This is not usually required on macOS.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="https://strawberryperl.com/">Strawberry Perl homepage</a>
    </div>
    <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-7.png" alt="Strawberry Perl"></figure>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="tip" class="callout-card">
  <p class="eyebrow">Tip</p>
  <h2>Automatic package installation</h2>
  <div class="doc-section-grid">
    <div>
      <p>When a package is missing during compilation, MiKTeX can prompt you to install it.</p>
      <p>Check the install box and continue to enable automatic package installation in the future.</p>
    </div>
    <figure class="image-frame"><img src="/assets/images/1.1.3-8.png" alt="Package auto-install dialog"></figure>
  </div>
</section>
